# .pii-allow -- real-world identifiers this repo is ALLOWED to contain.
#
# One literal per line, each with a reason. This is an allowlist with a written justification: it
# shows up in the diff and has to be argued for. That is the opposite of quietly widening a regex.
#
# Legitimate entries look like: a vendor's public sender address that a parser must recognize, or a
# public support line. NEVER put the operator's own data here -- if it is theirs, it does not belong
# in a public repo at all.
#
# Example:
#   noreply@vendor.example    # the sender address the classifier fixture must match
